# Debug Mode: Browser-Side Instrumentation

This project runs in a browser that **blocks direct `127.0.0.1` fetches** (CORS/mixed-content). Always route debug logs through the server proxy instead.

## REQUIRED: Use `/api/debug-log` for all browser-side fetch instrumentation

```js
// ✅ CORRECT — routes through Express proxy, works in browser
fetch('/api/debug-log', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    _debugUrl: 'http://127.0.0.1:PORT/ingest/UUID',
    _debugSessionId: 'SESSION_ID',
    sessionId: 'SESSION_ID',
    location: 'file.js:LINE',
    message: 'desc',
    data: { k: v },
    timestamp: Date.now(),
    hypothesisId: 'H-A',
  }),
}).catch(() => {});

// ❌ WRONG — blocked by browser security policy
fetch('http://127.0.0.1:7456/ingest/...', { ... });
```

The `_debugUrl` must start with `http://127.0.0.1:` and the server's `POST /api/debug-log` handler will forward it. The `X-Debug-Session-Id` header is **not** needed on the `/api/debug-log` call — put `_debugSessionId` in the body instead.
